    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "TO : The Director",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "FROM : D. M. Ladd",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING SAUCERS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "Reference is made to your inquiry on the attached routing slip:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "\"Just what are the facts re 'flying saucers'? A short",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "memo as to whether it is true or just what Air Force",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "etc. think of them.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "In response to your inquiry, Special Agent S. T. Reynolds obtained",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "the following information today (3/28/50) from Major Boggs and Lieutenant",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "Colonel J. V. Hearn of Air Force Intelligence. The Air Force discontinued",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "their intelligence project to determine what flying saucers are the latter part",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "of last year. They publicly announced to the press in December, 1949, that",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "the project had been discontinued. They advised that the press release had",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "been concurred in by the Army and Navy. The reason for the discontinuance,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "according to Major Boggs and Lieutenant Colonel Hearn, was that after two",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "years of investigation over three-fourths of the incidents regarding flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "saucers proved to be misidentifications of a wide variety of conventional",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "items such as lighted weather balloons and other air-borne objects.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Colonel Hearn pointed out that the Commanders of the various areas",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "are charged with the security of those areas. Reports concerning flying saucers",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "received at this time will be investigated by the Area Commander and his report",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "submitted to the Air Force Intelligence Division as an intelligence item.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "Major Boggs and Lieutenant Colonel Hearn made the observation that",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "many of the reported sightings of flying saucers at this time appear to be an out-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "growth of recent magazine articles. They reiterated that the Air Force is",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "conducting no active investigation to determine whether flying saucers exist",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "or what they might happen to be.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "You will recall that the investigation of flying saucers was discontinued",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "by the Bureau in October, 1947, in order that the Air Force could take over",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "such investigations. (62-83694-141-160)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "Attachment",
      "status": "image_matched"
